<div type="definition">
<p>AGRICULTURAL WORK INTENDING to REMOVE WEEDS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most current general ancient word for removing weeds is nòu 耨／鎒, and the word refers specifically to a short-handled iron tool as illustrated, and this tool became common in Warring States times. The handle, like all ancient handles, was short. Probably, it is a further development of the ancient bó 鎛</p>
<p>2. Chú 鋤／鉏／耡 is to remove weeds by hacking the earth with a tool of the illustrated kind with a long handle.</p>
<p>3. Bó 鎛 was an ancient short-handled hoe with a bronze head.</p>
        </div>
